AMERICAN FOUL BROOD, APIARY - SOUTH AFRICA (02): (WESTERN CAPE) OIE
*******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 3 Apr 2009
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2009; 22(15)
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=7962>


American foulbrood of honeybees, South Africa
---------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Apr 2009 from Mr Bothle Michael
Modisane, Assistant Director General, Department of Agriculture,
National Regulatory Services, Pretoria, South Africa

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 10 Feb 2009
Date of first confirmation of the event: 20 Feb 2009
Report date: 3 Apr 2009
Date submitted to OIE: 3 Apr 2009
Reason for notification: First occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Paenibacillus larvae_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 2
Outbreak location and affected population: Western Cape Province
(Ouderootkraal, Lakeside, Cape Metropol; Maitland, Maitland, Cape Metropol)
Total animals affected
Species: bees (hives)
Susceptible: 1240
Cases: 585
Deaths: 4
Destroyed: 15
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics:
Species: bees (hives)
Apparent morbidity rate: 47.18 percent
Apparent mortality rate: **
Apparent case fatality rate: *
Portions of susceptible animals lost: **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Agricultural Research Council, Plant
Protection Research Institute, Roodeplaat (national laboratory)
Tests and results
Species: bees
Test: polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date: 20 Feb 2009
Result: positive

Laboratory name and type: Idexx Laboratories, Johannesburg (private laboratory)
Tests and results
Species: bees
Test: bacteriological examination
Test date: 20 Mar 2009
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Tetracycline is a very suitable treatment for infected hives.
However, generally once a hive is infected the infection may be
cleared but it seems to return when certain conditions are right. - Mod.TG]

[A map of the outbreak locations is available at the source URL
above. - CopyEd.MJ]
